    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 04 Nov 2019 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://ducdauge.github.io/authors/emponti/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a prospective postdoctoral fellow at &lt;a href=&#34;https://mila.quebec/en/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Mila - Quebec AI Institute&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mcgill.ca/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;McGill University&lt;/a&gt; collaborating with &lt;a href=&#34;https://sivareddy.in/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Siva Reddy&lt;/a&gt;. I am expected to complete my Ph.D. in Computational Linguistics at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cam.ac.uk/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;University of Cambridge&lt;/a&gt;, where I was supervised by Prof. &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~alk23/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Anna Korhonen&lt;/a&gt;, in September 2020. I am also a frequent collaborator of Ryan Cotterell&amp;rsquo;s lab &lt;a href=&#34;https://rycolab.github.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Rycolab&lt;/a&gt; at ETH Zürich.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most of my research revolves around sample efficiency in Bayesian neural networks, with applications to resource-poor languages. How to endow models with the correct inductive bias to perform few-shot learning? How to exploit the modularity of knowledge to generalise to new domains where only few variables change? Moreover, I belive that text-based, distributional information reflects but a single facet of language. To address this, I helped create multilingual evaluation benchmarks for pure semantic knowledge, such as &lt;a href=&#34;https://multisimlex.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;MultiSimLex&lt;/a&gt;, and for causal reasoning, such as &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/cambridgeltl/xcopa&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;XCOPA&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Cambrige, I was affiliated to &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.joh.cam.ac.uk/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;St John&amp;rsquo;s College&lt;/a&gt;. I have previously interned as an AI/ML researcher at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.apple.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Apple&lt;/a&gt; in Cupertino. I won a &lt;a href=&#34;https://ai.google/research/outreach/faculty-research-awards/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Google Research Faculty Award&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mmll.cam.ac.uk/news/prof-anna-korhonens-project-enabling-multilingual-conversational-ai-awarded-erc-proof-concept&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;ERC Proof of Concept grant&lt;/a&gt; for projects co-written with my supervisor. I hold a bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree in modern literature (with a thesis on the partitive case in Finnish) from the &lt;a href=&#34;http://wcm-3.unipv.it/site/en/home.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;University of Pavia&lt;/a&gt;. During that time, I was also part of the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.iusspavia.it/home&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Institute for Advanced Study (I.U.S.S)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ghislieri.it/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Collegio Ghislieri&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
